32:
Everything will be fine. The rest of the
party went to get help. A healer should
be here any second.
33:
Rest. As long as you don't move,
you should be—
35: Dead in a half-hour, I'd reckon.
37:
Snakes 'round these parts've got some
nasty venom. Sorry, but that kid doesn't
have time to wait for a healer.
38:
Lucky for him, I think ahead. This here
antidote should tide him over.
46:
Ah, can that little nose'a yours smell
the blood on me? Don't worry about it.
Comes with the job.
48:
Or what? Not into the good Samaritan
act? I'd be happy to charge you for it
if it sounds too good to be tru—
59: Well aren't WE in a hurry now?
61:
How 'bout you? We'll talk after the kid's
stable.
70: Right then. I'll get to work.
86:
Light? Stella? Where... Where am I?
I was fighting, and then—
89: The monsters are gone. You're safe now.
97:
Yes. I cannot thank you enough for
your aid.
99:
You even kept a perimeter for us...
I haven't seen a single monster.
103:
I prefer not to bust my ass dealing with
every creepy and crawlie in the forest.
Easier to just pick 'em off from here.
106:
As promised, I would like to discuss your
reward. You have done us a great
service; I will do anything in my power
to repay it.
109:
Relax, relax. I'm not gonna bleed you
dry over an antidote. You guys're
adventurers, right?
111: I want in. Let me join your party.
117:
Well, bud, I want to do some adventurin',
but I can't go through the Guild for...
reasons.
119:
Reasons I'd prefer not to share.
So. What'll it be?
124:
What? Not gonna ask the girlie over
there first?
128:
You saved Alk. Regardless of your
circumstances, you are welcome here.
131: Well, then. Glad to be of help.
135:
I will warn you though... We have some
"circumstances" of our own.
141:
You'll see. Ever seen a sky with worlds
for stars?
